RIYADH: Global rating agency S&P is withdrawing all its credit ratings for Russian companies after a ban set by the European Union, Bloomberg reported. Following the Russian invasion of Ukraine, the EU imposed a deadline of Apr. 15 for all companies to pull out their credit grades for Russian-based firms. The rating of Russia's sovereign wealth fund by S&P is currently CC â€“ two levels above default, after being downgraded recently amid the ongoing conflict.